import{f as a}from"index-939d0dd8.js"/*tpa=https://cdn.w3cbus.com/mdui/design-1/assets/index-939d0dd8.js*/;const t={a1:"Tabs make it easy to explore and switch between different views.",a2:"Tabs enable content organization at a high level, such as switching between views, data sets, or functional aspects of an app.",a3:"Present tabs as a single row above their associated content. Tab labels should succinctly describe the content within.",a4:"Because swipe gestures are used for navigating between tabs, don't pair tabs with content that also supports swiping.",a5:"Types",a6:"Fixed<br />Scrollable",a7:"Tab labels",a8:"Tab labels may include icons and text.",a9:"Color",a10:"Apply your app’s accent color, or a contrasting color, to text fields and the text field cursor.",a11:"Usage",a12:"Content",a13:"Types of tabs",a14:"Specs",a15:"A tab provides the affordance for displaying grouped content. A tab label succinctly describes the tab’s associated grouping of content.",a16:"Mobile tabs",a17:"Default app bar and fixed tab bar",a18:"Extended app bar and fixed tab bar",a19:"Fixed tab bar pinned to top with scrolled content",a20:"Inset search, app bar, and fixed tab bar",a21:"Default app bar and scrollable tab bar",a22:"The text color is the same as the tab indicator.",a23:"Default app bar and fixed tab bar with icons",a24:"The icon color is the same as the tab indicator.",a25:"Desktop tabs",a26:"Default app and tab bars",a27:"Tabs with a More dropdown menu",a28:"Tabs with an expanded More dropdown menu",a29:"Tabs with Books selected from a More dropdown menu",a30:"Tabs with overflow pagination",a31:"Tabs with overflow pagination scrolled",a32:"Tab bar centered",a33:"When to use",a34:"Use tabs to organize content at a high level, for example, to present different sections of a newspaper. Don’t use tabs for carousels or pagination of content. Those use cases involve viewing content, not navigating between groups of content.",a35:`For more detail about using tabs for navigating top-level views, see “Tabs” in <a class="do-router" href="${a("/patterns/navigation.html#navigation-patterns")}">Navigation - Patterns</a>.`,a36:"Don't use tabs with content that supports the swipe gesture, because swipe gestures are used for navigating between tabs. For example, avoid using tabs in a map where content is pannable, or a list where items can be dismissed with a swipe.",a37:"Fixed tabs should be used with a limited number of tabs and when consistent placement will aid muscle memory. Scrollable tabs should be used when there are many or a variable number of tabs.",a38:"The tabs switch between equally important facets of store content.",a39:"The tabs switch between destinations of varied importance within the store.",a40:"Tab characteristics",a41:"Tabs control the display of content in a consistent location.",a42:"Formatting specifications:",a43:"Present tabs as a single row. Wrap tab labels to a second line if needed, and then truncate.",a44:"Do not include a set of tabbed content within a tab",a45:"Highlight the tab corresponding to the visible content",a46:"Group tabs together hierarchically. Connect a group of tabs with its content.",a47:"Keep tabs adjacent to their content to maintain the relationship between the two",a48:"Tabs are presented as a single row.",a49:"Tabs are not presented as a single column.",a50:"Use a content hierarchy such that tabs relate to the currently displayed content.",a51:"Tabs should not be nested.",a52:"Content presented in tabs can vary widely, even between tabs. For example, tabs showing different years of an artist’s portfolio or tabs containing different types of settings.",a53:"All content within a set of tabs should be related under a larger organizing principle (for example, Settings or Directions), with each tab’s content mutually exclusive of the others'.",a54:"Tab labels should provide meaningful distinctions that logically organize associated content.",a55:"Tab labels may include icons and text. When choosing a text label, use short titles.",a56:"Avoid the need for cross-tab comparison of content. Significant cross-tab comparison may indicate the content would benefit from a different organization or presentation that places the content closer together.",a57:"A long label exceeding the maximum width of a tab may wrap to a second line before being truncated.",a58:"Don't resize single-line labels. If labels are too long, wrap text across two lines or use scrollable tabs",a59:"Wrap labels before truncating them. Truncating labels too early can impede comprehension.",a60:"Do not combine text labels with icons. Use either all text labels or all icon labels.",a61:"Depending on the platform and the context of use, tabbed content can be presented as either fixed tabs or scrollable tabs.",a62:"Fixed tabs",a63:"Fixed tabs display all tabs concurrently and are best used with content that benefits from quick pivots between tabs in fixed positions, such as switching transportation methods for directions in Google Maps.",a64:"Fixed tabs have equal width, calculated either as the view width divided by the number of tabs, or based on the widest tab label. To navigate between fixed tabs, touch the tab or swipe the content area left or right.",a65:"Fixed tabs on mobile",a66:"Scrollable tabs",a67:"Scrollable tabs display a subset of tabs at any given moment. They can contain longer tab labels and a larger number of tabs than fixed tabs. Scrollable tabs are best used for browsing contexts in touch interfaces when users don’t need to directly compare the tab labels.",a68:"To navigate between scrollable tabs, touch the tab or swipe the content area left or right. To scroll the tabs without navigating, swipe the tabs left or right.",a69:"Scrollable tabs on mobile",a70:"Examples of scrollable tabs",a71:"Fixed tabs",a72:"The width of each tab can be calculated by taking the width of the view and dividing it by the number of tabs. Alternatively, make all tabs the width of the largest tab.",a73:"If the margin between the tab edge and view edge is 16dp or less, use full-width tabs instead of centered tabs.",a74:"Width minimum and maximum (inclusive of padding)",a75:"Maximum: 264dp",a76:"Minimum: 160dp for larger views, 72 dp for smaller views",a77:"Height",a78:"Padding",a79:"12dp left and right of text",a80:"20dp from bottom for a single line of text, 12dp from bottom for two lines of text",a81:"Alignment",a82:"Full-width for smaller views",a83:"Centered for larger views",a84:"Indicator",a85:"Height: 2dp",a86:"Color: #fff or accent color",a87:"Fixed tabs on mobile, text only, portrait orientation",a88:"Mobile portrait example of fixed tabs, text only",a89:"Tabs with text only",a90:"Text",a91:"12sp when wrapped across a maximum of two lines",a92:"All caps",a93:"Horizontally and vertically centered",a94:"Active color: #fff or accent color",a95:"Unfocused tab color: #fff 70%",a96:"Mobile landscape example of same tabs aligned with left keyline",a97:"Mobile landscape example of same tabs centered",a98:"Tabs with icons and text",a99:"Height",a100:"Icon",a101:"Content alignment",a102:"Text and icon are centered horizontally in the tab",a103:"Padding",a104:"10dp between icon and text",a105:"16dp under text",a106:"Fixed tabs on mobile, icons and text",a107:"Tabs with icons only",a108:"Icon is centered horizontally and vertically in the tab",a109:"12dp under icon",a110:"Fixed tabs on mobile, icons only",a111:"Scrollable tabs",a112:"The left-most tab content aligns with the keyline. Alignment varies between landscape and portrait to match the different keylines.",a113:"The width of each tab is independently calculated.",a114:"Width minimum and maximum (inclusive of padding)",a115:"Maximum (whichever fits and is smaller): 264dp or (the value of view size minus 56dp)",a116:"Minimum: 160dp for larger views, 72 dp for smaller views",a117:"12dp left and right of text",a118:"20dp from bottom for a single line of text, 12dp from bottom for two lines of text",a119:"Scrollable tab",a120:"Extremely long tab labels, as shown here, should be avoided. This max-width scrollable tab contains wrapped text.",a121:"Text",a122:"12sp when wrapped across a maximum of two lines",a123:"All caps",a124:"Vertically and horizontally centered",a125:"Active color: #fff or accent color",a126:"Unfocused tab color: #fff 70%",a127:"Extremely long tab labels, as shown here, should be avoided. These max-width tabs, depicted in landscape mode on mobile, are aligned with the left keyline.",a128:"Desktop",a129:"Width minimum and maximum (inclusive of padding)",a130:"Maximum (whichever fits and is smaller): 264dp or (the value of view size minus 56dp)",a131:"Minimum: 160dp for larger views, 72 dp for smaller views",a132:"Height",a133:"Alignment",a134:"Centered or aligned with left keyline",a135:"Text",a136:"All caps",a137:"Horizontally and vertically centered",a138:"Wraps across a maximum of two lines",a139:"Active color: #fff or accent color",a140:"Unfocused tab color: #fff 70%",a141:"Padding",a142:"24dp left and right of text",a143:"20dp from bottom for a single line of text, 12dp from bottom for two lines of text",a144:"First tab text left padding: 80dp",a145:"Indicator",a146:"Height: 2dp",a147:"Color: #fff or accent color",a148:"Desktop tabs",a149:"Tab touch target animation",a150:"Note: Implementations of this component may vary by platform. By using standard platform implementations, you will receive related future improvements.",a151:"Animation of tab touch target.",a152:"Material Design tabs for easy view exploration",a153:"Material Design default app bar with fixed tab bar",a154:"Material Design: Extended app bar with fixed tabs",a155:"Material Design fixed tab bar with scrolling content",a156:"Material Design inset search and fixed tab bar",a157:"Material Design default app bar with scrollable tabs",a158:"Text color matches the tab indicator in Material Design",a159:"Material Design app bar and fixed tab bar with icons",a160:"Icon color matches the tab indicator in Material Design",a161:"Default app and tab bars in Material Design",a162:"Material Design Tabs with More dropdown menu",a163:"Material Design Tabs with expanded More dropdown",a164:"Material Design Tabs with Books from More menu",a165:"Material Design tabs with overflow pagination",a166:"Material Design tabs with overflow pagination scrolled",a167:"Centered tab bar in Material Design",a168:"Material Design tabs for switching content facets",a169:"Material Design tabs for navigating store destinations",a170:"Material Design Tabs in a single row",a171:"Material Design tabs are not shown in a single column",a172:"Material Design: Tabs should match displayed content",a173:"Tabs should not be nested in Material Design",a174:"Material Design: Long tab label may wrap to second line",a175:"Material Design: Avoid resizing single-line labels",a176:"Wrap labels for better clarity in Material Design",a177:"Material Design: Use text labels or icons, not both",a178:"Material Design: Fixed tabs for mobile",a179:"Material Design: Fixed tabs for mobile",a180:"Scrollable tabs example in Material Design",a181:"Scrollable tabs example in Material Design",a182:"Material Design fixed tabs, text only, mobile portrait",a183:"Material Design mobile portrait with fixed text tabs",a184:"Mobile tabs aligned with left keyline in Material Design",a185:"Mobile landscape example of centered tabs in Material Design",a186:"Material Design fixed tabs with icons and text for mobile",a187:"Material Design fixed tabs with icons and text on mobile",a188:"Material Design: Fixed mobile tabs with icons only",a189:"Material Design fixed mobile tabs with icons only",a190:"Scrollable tab in Material Design",a191:"Scrollable tab with wrapped text, avoiding long labels - Material Design",a192:"Long tab labels should be avoided in Material Design",a193:"Material Design desktop tabs"};export{t as en};
